item.caption: MR CERVICAL SPINE WO CONTRAST (2023-05-11 9:31 PM EST)

paragraph.content: Multilevel multifactorial cervical spondylosis, slightly progressed compared to MRI cervical spine 2019-12-04. In summary:
* At C3-C4, there is moderate right and mild left neuroforaminal narrowing.
* At C4-C5, there is moderate spinal canal stenosis and mild bilateral neuroforaminal narrowing.
* At C5-C6, there is moderate spinal canal stenosis, mild right neuroforaminal narrowing, and moderate left neuroforaminal narrowing.
* At C6-C7, there is moderate to severe right and mild to moderate left neuroforaminal narrowing.
* At C7-T1, there is moderate left neuroforaminal narrowing.
Robin Robinson, MD 2023-05-14 11:14 AM
PROCEDURE: MR CERVICAL SPINE WO CONTRAST 2023-05-11 9:08 PM
INDICATIONS: 69-year-old man with neck pain.
TECHNIQUE: Multiplanar, multisequence MRI of the cervical spine was obtained without intravenous contrast per department protocol.
COMPARISON: MRI cervical spine 2019-12-04
FINDINGS:

There is straightening of the usual cervical lordosis. Vertebral body height's and alignment are maintained. There is mild diffuse disc desiccation without significant loss of disc height. There is no evidence of acute fracture or malalignment. There is mild diffuse heterogeneity of the marrow signal without identification of the suspicious marrow replacing lesion on this noncontrast enhanced examination.
The cervical spinal cord demonstrates normal morphology and signal.
The prevertebral and posterior paraspinal soft tissues are unremarkable.
Segmental analysis:
Craniocervical junction: Unremarkable.
C2-C3: There is no significant posterior disc protrusion, spinal canal stenosis, or neuroforaminal narrowing.

C3-C4: There is a small broad-based posterior disc protrusion. There is bilateral facet arthropathy and uncovertebral hypertrophy. There is no significant spinal canal stenosis. There is moderate right and mild left neuroforaminal narrowing.

C4-C5: There is a broad-based posterior disc protrusion. There is bilateral facet arthropathy and uncovertebral hypertrophy. There is ligamentum flavum hypertrophy. There is moderate spinal canal stenosis. There is mild bilateral neuroforaminal narrowing. These findings are mildly progressed compared to prior imaging.

C5-C6: There is a broad-based, mildly eccentric left posterior disc protrusion. There is bilateral facet arthropathy and uncovertebral hypertrophy. There is moderate spinal canal stenosis. There is mild right and moderate left neuroforaminal narrowing. These findings are mildly progressed compared to prior imaging.

C6-C7: There is a broad-based posterior disc protrusion. There is bilateral facet arthropathy and uncovertebral hypertrophy. There is no significant spinal canal stenosis. There is moderate to severe right and mild to moderate left neuroforaminal narrowing. These findings are not significantly changed.

C7-T1: There is a small broad-based posterior disc protrusion. There is left facet arthropathy and uncovertebral hypertrophy. There is no significant spinal canal stenosis or right neuroforaminal narrowing. There is moderate left neuroforaminal narrowing, progressed compared to prior imaging.
T1-T2: There is no significant posterior disc protrusion, spinal canal stenosis, or neuroforaminal narrowing.
T2-T3: Limited evaluation, imaged in the sagittal plane only. Within this limitation, there is no significant spinal canal stenosis.

item.caption: US KIDNEY/RENAL AND BLADDER (2023-03-29 9:07 AM EDT)

paragraph.content: No sonographic finding to explain the patient's pain.

Left renal cyst, without significant change in size from 2016, however, there is a septation visible by ultrasound with some possible vascularity. Given the stability in size, this is likely benign, however, follow-up is recommended with ultrasound in 6 months to assess for any concerning change.

Clayton Stewart, MD 2023-03-29 10:51 AM
PROCEDURE: US KIDNEY/RENAL AND BLADDER 2023-03-29 7:24 AM
COMPARISON: Prior CTs
INDICATION: rt sided flank pain
TECHNIQUE:
Real time sonographic images with grayscale and color Doppler ultrasound were obtained of the bilateral kidneys.
FINDINGS:
The urinary bladder is fluid-filled and normal in appearance. Bilateral ureteral jets are demonstrated.
Prevoid urinary bladder volume is 594 cc. Postvoid volume is 27 cc.
The right kidney measures 9.8 cm. There is no right hydronephrosis, shadowing renal calculus or focal cortical thinning.

The left kidney measures 11.2 cm. There is no left hydronephrosis, shadowing renal calculus or focal cortical thinning. There is a an approximately 1.5 cm interpolar cyst, which contains thin internal septation, with possible associated vascularity.
The visualized portion of the liver is echogenic, consistent with hepatocellular disease, most commonly hepatic steatosis.
